  "narrative": "DRIVER\nNZD leads H4 CSM at 100 with a 60-point divergence from D1 (40), flagging this as the single most important short-term signal \u2014 USD bears from US-Iran peace deal flow and DXY at 99.01 are accelerating commodity-linked currencies in a genuine H4 regime flip to risk-on. NZDUSD and AUDUSD are the cleanest expressions with AUDJPY as the amplifier, supported by AUDUSD-AUDJPY correlation of 0.90 and NZDJPY-NZDUSD at 0.89 confirming cross-yen alignment. CHF H4 CSM fading from 100 to 77 while USDCHF H4 prints strong sell -6 makes short USDCHF the defensive hedge against any USD snap-back.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: AUDJPY H4 momentum 56 rising sharply, D1 stable at 53, both timeframes aligned\nFading: EURUSD D1 at 25 falling hard, GBPUSD D1 at 24 falling hard, USDJPY H4 44 dropping\n\nWATCH\nUS-Iran negotiation headline escalation hits USDCAD directly, oil supply repricing drives CAD strength and confirms D1 buy signal reversal\nAsian session open tests NZDUSD continuation above current structure, H4 strong buy with NZD CSM divergence intact triggers extension toward weekly highs\nAUDJPY H4 strong buy -6 signal retests intraday support, break holds confirms risk-on regime acceleration and validates AUD CSM rank at 88",
